text: Tuscaloosa County is a county of the U.S. state of Alabama."ACES Winston County Office" (links/history),Alabama Cooperative Extension System (ACES), 2007, webpage:ACES-Tuscaloosa. It was named in honor of the Choctaw chief Tuskaloosa. In 2020, 227,036 people lived there. == References == Category:1818 establishments in Alabama Territory
title: Tuscaloosa County, Alabama
